+### stdout-leaking git wrapper
+
+A git wrapper on PATH may write progress to stdout even when `git --quiet`
+is used. `antidote-script` should not leak that text into the generated
+plugin script.
+
+```zsh
+% function git { print 'NOISY_GIT_STDOUT'; mockgit "$@" }
+% output=$(antidote-script --kind zsh foo/bar 2>/dev/null)
+% print -r -- $output | grep 'NOISY_GIT_STDOUT'  #=> --exit 1
+% print -r -- $output | subenv ANTIDOTE_HOME
+fpath+=( "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/foo/bar" )
+source "$ANTIDOTE_HOME/foo/bar/bar.plugin.zsh"
+% function git { mockgit "$@" }
+%
+```
+
